                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/<hi rend="superscript">4014/s</hi>
                </note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chief of Naval Operations (<persName type="from"
                            >Pratt</persName>) to the Commander in Chief, United States Asiatic
                        Fleet (<persName corresp="#p_TAMM1" type="to">Taylor</persName>)</hi>
                    <note n="46" xml:id="d219fn46">Copy of telegram transmitted to the Department by
                        the Navy Department on February 3.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-02-03T14:00:00-05:00"
                            >February 3, 1932—2 p.m.</date>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>When you confer with British military and naval authorities please assure them of
                    100 percent naval and military cooperation with them in preserving the
                    neutrality and safety of the International Settlement at Shanghai.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
